<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 03 at 9:25AM EDT  by NWS Grand Rapids</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Kent and
northeastern Ottawa Counties through 1030 AM EDT...
At 925 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Coopersville, or 13 miles northwest of Grand Rapids, moving northeast
at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Walker...              Rockford...            Sparta...
Cedar Springs...       Conklin...             Wright...
Kent City...           Sand Lake...           Crockery Lake...
Belmont...             Marne...               Comstock Park...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
